'''Shimazu Kuni no Miyatsuko''' (島津国造, also read as Shimazu Kokuzō) was a [[:en:Kuni no miyatsuko|kuni no miyatsuko]] (provincial governor) governing the [[:en:Shima Province|Shima Province]].
== Overview == === Ancestry === According to the ''[[:en:Kujiki|Sendai Kuji Hongi]]'' ("Kuni no Miyatsuko Hongi" section), during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Seimu|Emperor Seimu]], {{ill|Izumo Kasaya no Mikoto|ja|出雲笠夜命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izumo Kasaya no Mikoto|qq=}}, the grandson of {{ill|Sahini Ashini|ja|佐比邇足尼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sahini Ashini|qq=}}, who was also an ancestor of the {{ill|Izumo clan|lt=Izumo clan|lt=Izumo no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|Izumo Province 造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izumo no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, was appointed as Shimazu Kuni no Miyatsuko.
=== Clan === The Shimazu Kuni no Miyatsuko belonged to the {{ill|Shima clan|ja|島氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shima clan|qq=}} (Shima-uji, with the title {{ill|Ason (title)|ja|直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ason (title)|qq=}}). They were related to the {{ill|Futakata Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|二方国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Futakata Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}. Even after the end of the [[:en:Kuni no miyatsuko|kuni no miyatsuko]] system, they continued to serve as {{ill|gunryō|ja|郡領|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/gunryō|qq=}} (district governors) in {{ill|Tōshi District|ja|答志郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōshi District|qq=}} during the [[:en:Middle Ages|Medieval Japan]].<ref>Ryo Ota, "Shima," in ''Seishi Kakeizu Daijiten'' (1936), p. 2846.</ref> Based on genealogies and entries in the ''Kuni no Miyatsuko Hongi,'' they are generally regarded as related to the {{ill|Izumo Omi|ja|出雲臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izumo Omi|qq=}}.
== Territory == === Governed Region === The territory governed by the Shimazu Kuni no Miyatsuko corresponds to the area known in ancient times as "Shima (津) Province," later becoming [[:en:Shima Province|Shima Province]], now the {{ill|Shima region|ja|志摩地方|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shima region|qq=}} of [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]].
== Patron Deity == The clan's deity is enshrined at the [[:en:Izawa-no-miya|Ise Grand Shrine]], the [[:en:Ichinomiya|Ichinomiya]] (highest-Ranking shrine) of Shima Province, located in the former {{ill|Tōshi District|ja|答志郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōshi District|qq=}}.
=== Associated Shrines === * [[:en:Saminaga Shrine|Saminaga Shrine]] *: Located in {{ill|Isobe, Mie|ja|磯部町恵利原|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isobe, Mie|qq=}}, [[:en:Shima, Mie|Shima City]], this is a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}. Like their relatives the {{ill|Futakata Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|二方国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Futakata Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, they worshipped {{ill|Toshigami|lt=Toshigami|lt=Ōtoshi no Kami|ja|大歳神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtoshi no Kami|qq=}}.<ref name="houga" />
